<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911223-0029</DOCNO><DOCID>911223-0029.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- American Cyanamid Co.:   Separate Unit Is Formed   For Chemicals Businesses</HL><DATE>12/23/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19</SO><CO>   ACY</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>COMMODITY CHEMICALS (CHC)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><NS>RESTRUCTURINGS, RECAPITALIZATION (RCN)</NS><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   American Cyanamid Co., Wayne, N.J., said it isconsolidating its chemicals businesses into a separate unit.   The move is the latest in a series of restructurings inthe chemicals industry. The highly cyclical industry has beensuffering for more than a year from excess capacity and theeconomy's slowdown.</LP><TEXT>   Cyanamid's restructuring indicates the company may intendto spin off the consolidated chemicals unit, in whole or inpart. &quot;It may be appropriate for this new chemicals entity tohave some form of public ownership in the future,&quot; Cyanamidsaid.   Still, Cyanamid said, its &quot;first objective is to establisha strong autonomous chemical organization.&quot; The restructuringannouncement sent Cyanamid shares up $1 to close at $60.25 inNew York Stock Exchange composite trading Friday.   For 1991, Cyanamid said its chemicals operation will haveoperating earnings of about $30 million, on sales of about$1.1 billion, Cyanamid said.   Cyanamid also said the restructuring will let it focus onits medical and agricultural operations.</TEXT></DOC>